lv.emes.libraries.tools.lists

Interface IPerambulateListActions<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - type of list elements.
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IListActions<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    MS_List, MS_StringList

    public interface IPerambulateListActions<T>
    Interface defines methods for list that can be perambulated. Methods:
    -first; -next; -prev; -last -currentIndexInsideTheList; -current
    Version:
    1.2.

    • Method Detail

      • count

        int count()
        Returns:
        count of elements in list. [0..+]

      • getIndexOfCurrent

        int getIndexOfCurrent()
        Index of current element. Returns -1 when reached end of list.
        Returns:
        [-1..count-1] Value depends on use of first, next, prev and last.

      • get

        T get(int aIndex)
        Gets element by index.
        Parameters:
        aIndex - index of element in the list.
        Returns:
        element of type T.

      • setIndexOfCurrent

        void setIndexOfCurrent(int aIndexOfCurrent)
        Sets the position of current element in the list.
        Parameters:
        aIndexOfCurrent - index of current element. Used in perambulation purposes. Pass -1 to set reference to end of list!

      • current

        T current()
        Returns current element.
        Returns:
        null if element not found in the list.

      • first

        void first()
        Points indexOfCurrent to first element of the list. If list is empty then indexOfCurrent = -1.

      • last

        void last()
        Points indexOfCurrent to last element of the list. If list is empty then indexOfCurrent = -1.

      • next

        void next()
        Try to increase value of indexOfCurrent by 1 to move forward. If indexOfCurrent = count then currentIndexInsideTheList = false.

      • prev

        void prev()
        Try to decrease value of indexOfCurrent by 1 to move backward. If indexOfCurrent = -1 then currentIndexInsideTheList = false.

      • currentIndexInsideTheList

        default boolean currentIndexInsideTheList()
        Tests whether current element is inside the list.
        Returns:
        returns true if current element is still in the list. Returns false if by perambulation process all the list is walked through.

      • doWithEveryItem

        default void doWithEveryItem(IFuncSomeAction<T> action)
        Walks through all the elements in list and does the defined action action.
        Parameters:
        action - method that describes the actions that every element must do. Method's incoming parameter is every item of the list.
